CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 18, 1954, pg. 10 reads: "New UL Guild Officers - Pictured in Pittsburgh at the close of the recent National Conference of the Urban League are new officers of the League Guild. Seated: Mrs. Rose Butler, Milwaukee, treasurer; Mrs. Lillian Balenger, St. Paul, Minn., president; Mrs. Mary Alice Wilcox, Grand Rapids, Mich.  Standing: Mollie Moon, New York City, former president of the guild and now director of public relations and coordinator for the Council of Urban League Guilds, and Mrs. Eleanor Florence, Cleveland, Ohio, secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of League Guild officers, seated: Rose Butler, Lillian Balenger, and Mary Alice Wilcox; standing: Mollie Moon and Eleanor Florence, posed at table during National Conference of the Urban League
